description:
Responsibility
- Execute regular purchasing duties, e.g. PO processing, price negotiation, vendor sourcing, etc.;
- Co-ordinate with other departments and suppliers in the purchasing scope of work;
- Monitor the service, quality, price, on-time delivery and reliability of the suppliers.
- Perform other duties as assigned.


Requirement
Academic Qualification: Bachelor Degree holder or above;
Field of Study: Logistic / Supply Chain Management / Manufacturing / Engineering / Business Administration or other relevant discipline;
Years of Experience: 1 - 3 years of related working experience;
*Fresh graduate will also be considered.
- Knowledgeable and hands-on experience in SAP & MS Office.
- Effective communication skill with good command of written and spoken English & Chinese.

Fringe Benefit
- Double Pay;
- Incentive Bonus;
- 5-days Work;
- 12-19 days annual leave;
- Medical, Dental & Life Insurance Scheme.

Application Method
Interested parties please click "APPLY NOW" or send your application with the title & expected salary to HK Human Resources via Application E-mail.

All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only. Only short-listed candidates will be contacted for interview.

Responsibilities:


Responsible for direct and indirect materials and general supplies (including but not limited to equipment, automation, spare parts, facilities, service, etc.) sourcing and purchasing operations;
Set up target of purchasing functions and responsible for budget preparation;
Develop, assess, evaluate and manage suppliers' performance;
Negotiate price and manage contract with the suppliers;
Closely monitor and ensure the purchasing order management runs smoothly and efficiently;
Monitor goods quality and follow up delivery;
Improve the process of purchasing flow, system and operation;
Support RFQ and suppliers selection;
Lead, coach and strengthen the team to meet the requirement of internal customers;
Perform material and BOM price analysis, and prepare related reports;
Conduct continuous material cost reduction;
Keep update with the supplier market trend;
Perform ad-hoc activities as required.

Requirements:


Degree or above in Business Administration, Engineering, Purchasing or Supply Chain Management;
Minimum 8 years solid experience, with at least 3 years in management position, in sourcing and purchasing of direct electronics components and general purchasing in sizeable or multinational manufacturing companies;
Good component and product knowledge with proven record in handling electronics OEM/ ODM projects in areas of sourcing, supplier selection and certification, procurement and supplier performance management;
Hands on experience in MRP system operation;
Expert at negotiation skills with suppliers for terms, conditions, lead-time and cost down;
Positive working attitude, self-motivated, responsible, good communication skill and a good team player;
Good analytical and negotiation skills;
Result-oriented, able to work independently and under pressure;
Good command of spoken and written English;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Purchasing Manager.
Interested candidates, please contact us at 59189131 for company details before applying.

Responsibilities :

Responsible for and support order & sales management of product line(s) assigned;
Assist in inventory management and analysis to achieve company target;
Coordinate among internal & external parties to ensure an efficient and timely order process;
Prepare various reports & analysis to vendors and internal management for review

Requirements:

University graduate with 2 years working experience preferred;
Detail-minded, self- motivated and good interpersonal skills;
Good numerical and analytical sense;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficient PC skills in MS office, especially Excel;
Fresh graduate will also be considered 

We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate.  Interested parties, please send us your resume with current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now". 

For more information about Synnex, please visit http://www.synnex.com.hk

All information will be treated in strict confidence and will be used exclusively for recruitment related purpose only

