Key Responsibilities:

Sourcing different materials or services to meet business needs.
Price negotiation and comparison among various vendors and suppliers, aiming to minimize cost whilst maximizing quality.
Liaise with customer, factory, forwarder, and other parties regarding sales and purchases and the related shipments;
Coordinate and follow up all transport and delivery arrangements
Cooperate the Commercial Manager to handle shipment with customer, factory and forwarder;
Handles I/E documentation, custom declaration, scheduling, logistics and distribution functions;
Assist to support to purchasing/logistic activities and ad-hoc project if necessary.

Requirements:

F.5/ DSE graduate or above;
1 year relevant experience, preferable from trading/manufacturing sector (Fresh graduate will also be considered);
Knowledge of Import/ Export documentation, custom declaration, scheduling and logistic arrangement;
Good command in both English and Mandarin;
Familiar with MS office including Word, Excel, Knowledge of custom declaration software will be an advantage;
Strong communication and negotiation skills;
Pro-active, responsible and able to work under pressure;
Immediate availability is highly preferred.
